          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathscr {F}]]></fr:tex> be a coherent analytic sheaf on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X^*]]></fr:tex>, given as the restriction to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X^*]]></fr:tex> of a coherent analytic sheaf <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathscr {F}']]></fr:tex> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>.
    We define the <fr:em>meromorphic direct image</fr:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[j_*^\mathrm {m}\mathscr {F}]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathscr {F}]]></fr:tex> to be the inductive limit
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[       j_*^\mathrm {m}\mathscr {F}       = \varinjlim \mathscr {F}'(nY).     ]]></fr:tex></fr:p>
            <fr:p>Locally on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Y]]></fr:tex> is the sum of a finite family <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(Y_i)_{i\in  I}]]></fr:tex> of smooth divisors, and we define the <fr:em>pole-order filtration</fr:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex> on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[j_*^\mathrm {m}\mathcal {O}_X^*]]></fr:tex> by the equation

    <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>1370</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-ii-3.1.10.1</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-ii-3.1.10.1.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Equation</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>3.1.10.1</fr:number></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[         P^p(j_*^\mathrm {m}\mathcal {O}_{X^*})         = \sum _{n\in  A_p} \mathcal {O}_X\left (\sum (n_i+1)Y_i\right )       \tag{3.1.10.1}       ]]></fr:tex></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>

    where
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[       A_p       = \left \{(n_i)_{i\in  I} \mid  \sum _i n_i\leqslant  -p \text { and } n_i\geqslant 0\text { for all } i\right \}.     ]]></fr:tex>
    This construction globalises by endowing <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[j_*^\mathrm {m}\mathcal {O}_{X^*}]]></fr:tex> with an exhaustive filtration such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P^p=0]]></fr:tex> for <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p>0]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>We define the <fr:em>pole-order filtration</fr:em> of the complex <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[j_*^\mathrm {m}\Omega _{X^*}^\bullet =j_*^\mathrm {m}\mathcal {O}_{X^*}\otimes \Omega _X^\bullet ]]></fr:tex> to be the filtration

    <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>1371</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-ii-3.1.10.2</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-ii-3.1.10.2.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Equation</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>3.1.10.2</fr:number></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[         P^p(j_*^\mathrm {m}\Omega _{X^*}^k)         = P^{p-k}(j_*^\mathrm {m}\mathcal {O}_X)\otimes \Omega _X^k.       \tag{3.1.10.2}       ]]></fr:tex></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:p>
            <fr:p>The filtration <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex> induces, on the subcomplex <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Omega _X^\bullet \langle  Y\rangle ]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[j_*^\mathrm {m}\Omega _{X^*}^\bullet ]]></fr:tex>, the stupid filtration by the <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\sigma _{\geqslant  p}(\Omega _X^\bullet \langle  Y\rangle )]]></fr:tex>, which we also call the <fr:em>Hodge filtration</fr:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
